Table 7. Reported Voting and Registration of Family Members, by Age and Family Income: November 2020
1 'No response to registration' includes those who were not asked if they were registered as well as those who responded 'Don't Know,' and 'Refused.'
2 'No response to voting' includes those who were not asked if they voted as well as those who responded  'Don't Know,' and 'Refused.'

Note: Table 7 is limited to persons who report income or refuse to answer the question. Respondents who report not knowing their income are not included in this table, which includes only the reference person with relatives in the household or people with the following relationship to the householder: spouse, child, grandchild, parent, sibling, or other relative. This table excludes foster children, unmarried partners, non-relatives, and roommates.
Estimates may not sum to totals due to rounding.
For information on confidentiality protection, sampling error, nonsampling error, and definitions, see https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/cps/technical-documentation/complete.2020.html
Source: U.S. Census Bureau, Current Population Survey, November 2020
